fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.priority

Annotation Type Priority


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Priority
    Annotation that is used to configure the priority of an implementation.

    A developer that provides an implementation for a MessageSender or a TemplateParser should indicate the priority of its implementation. This way the result of MessagingBuilder is deterministic (always the same result).

    However, in a pluggable system, the value set by the developer may not fit the behavior needed by the user of the library. That's why the developer can provide a default value and a list of property keys.

    If a property is set, the user of the library can change the priority so if there are several implementations that are suitable to send the message, the selected one can be changed.

    The other advantage is that the registration priority of the Configurers are independent of the priority of the MessageSender and TemplateParser implementations.

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      int defaultValue

    • Element Detail

      • properties

        public abstract String[] properties
        The list of declared property keys of the form "${property.key}".

        If several property keys are registered, the first as a higher priority.

        If no property is registered, then the priority is not configurable.

        Returns:
        the property keys
        Default:
        {}

      • defaultValue

        public abstract int defaultValue
        If no property is declared or no value is set for declared properties, the default value is used as the priority.

        This value is generally set directly by the developer of the implementation.

        Returns:
        the default priority
        Default:
        0
